1
00:00:06,833 --> 00:00:09,542
- [guards grunting]
- [Daredevil grunting, yelling]

2
00:00:11,792 --> 00:00:14,559
[Matt] <i>That boat was full of weapons,
launchers and rifles.</i>

3
00:00:14,583 --> 00:00:16,726
<i>He's using the Freeport to smuggle arms.</i>

4
00:00:16,750 --> 00:00:18,518
[Sheila] <i>The wreck's
blocking the entrance.</i>

5
00:00:18,542 --> 00:00:20,934
<i>Nothing is landing till
the</i> Northern Star<i>'s cleared.</i>

6
00:00:20,958 --> 00:00:22,393
This is a terrorist attack.

7
00:00:22,417 --> 00:00:25,684
The hunt for Daredevil,
Karen Page. Intensify it.

8
00:00:25,708 --> 00:00:29,518
The people I work for
are grateful for the use of your port.

9
00:00:29,542 --> 00:00:32,559
But this has gone into,
like, eight kinds of wrong.

10
00:00:32,583 --> 00:00:35,018
There's an email on this card.

11
00:00:35,042 --> 00:00:37,250
Not everything I write is under my name.

12
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:39,601
[Fisk] <i>I imagine that you know</i>

13
00:00:39,625 --> 00:00:42,518
<i>who in my staff is loyal and who is not.</i>

14
00:00:42,542 --> 00:00:45,226
- [gun cocks and fires]
- [people screaming]

15
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:47,601
Achilleo and Christofi
are in a lot of trouble.

16
00:00:47,625 --> 00:00:48,893
Task Force took him.

17
00:00:48,917 --> 00:00:49,976
Where's Christofi?

18
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,226
[Achilleo] I don't know.

19
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:52,417
- [gun fires]
- [groans]

20
00:00:53,167 --> 00:00:55,393
- [man] <i>Sorry about your client, Murdock.</i>
- [Matt] <i>Me too.</i>

21
00:00:55,417 --> 00:00:56,893
They killed him. The police.

22
00:00:56,917 --> 00:00:59,250
- I'm sorry.
- I hate them, Mister Murdock.

23
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:02,684
[grunting]

24
00:01:02,708 --> 00:01:04,333
[shallow breathing]

25
00:01:08,458 --> 00:01:10,958
[gasps, breathing heavily]

26
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:19,792
[spray paint can rattles]

27
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:27,708
[sirens wailing in distance]

28
00:02:11,708 --> 00:02:14,125
[sirens wailing]

29
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:41,667
Can I help you?

30
00:02:48,833 --> 00:02:49,833
Can I help you?

31
00:02:51,083 --> 00:02:52,809
[Dex] There a nun who works here?

32
00:02:52,833 --> 00:02:55,250
Sister Maggie, I think.

33
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:58,750
[man] Yes, she's on a sabbatical year
in Rome.

34
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:01,333
[Dex] Father, I--

35
00:03:03,292 --> 00:03:05,042
I need absolution.

36
00:03:06,542 --> 00:03:08,125
I've betrayed people.

37
00:03:09,458 --> 00:03:11,042
I've betrayed myself.

38
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:12,833
[man] Oh, uh...

39
00:03:13,375 --> 00:03:15,393
I'm not technically a priest yet.

40
00:03:15,417 --> 00:03:17,875
I can't administer
the sacrament of Penance, but...

41
00:03:20,417 --> 00:03:21,875
I'm not too picky.

42
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:32,684
One. One-two. One-two.
One-two. One-two, slip.

43
00:03:32,708 --> 00:03:34,976
- Body.
- [both grunting]

44
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,059
Time!

45
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:37,726
[Fisk panting]

46
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:39,292
Sir, I need to talk to you.

47
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:41,083
What happened?

48
00:03:41,667 --> 00:03:43,625
The cop in Hell's Kitchen.

49
00:03:44,208 --> 00:03:45,583
Daredevil was there.

50
00:03:46,333 --> 00:03:48,042
Thirty-second break. No more.

51
00:03:48,542 --> 00:03:50,417
Gotta get you ready for fight night.

52
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:52,184
The cop's in hospital.

53
00:03:52,208 --> 00:03:55,000
- Good.
- Well, he had a heart attack.

54
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,417
Four Task Force, dead.

55
00:03:58,792 --> 00:04:00,333
Daredevil got away.

56
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:02,958
Apparently, someone is helping him.

57
00:04:03,583 --> 00:04:05,333
Someone with very good aim.

58
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:08,583
Poindexter.

59
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:11,458
[trainer] You giving up?
Not like you, man.

60
00:04:11,833 --> 00:04:13,143
Not like you at all.

61
00:04:13,167 --> 00:04:14,934
I thought you were tougher than that.

62
00:04:14,958 --> 00:04:17,458
- [Fisk yelling]
- [trainer groans]

63
00:04:20,792 --> 00:04:22,792
[♪ theme music playing]

64
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:02,726
[vehicle horns blaring]

65
00:06:02,750 --> 00:06:04,208
Okay. Thank you.

66
00:06:05,625 --> 00:06:07,458
Cherry's stable at Metro General.

67
00:06:09,042 --> 00:06:11,167
But the Task Force
can still get to him there.

68
00:06:11,625 --> 00:06:13,000
Yeah, I'll get eyes on him.

69
00:06:13,708 --> 00:06:15,309
Why was Bullseye even there?

70
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:16,333
I don't know.

71
00:06:17,083 --> 00:06:18,476
He could have killed me.

72
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:20,226
- Like the Task Force.
- But he didn't.

73
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:21,309
So, what is that?

74
00:06:21,333 --> 00:06:23,500
Is he just crazy,
or does he have a reason?

75
00:06:23,917 --> 00:06:26,476
Well, killing Task Force
only helps Fisk. Right?

76
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:28,018
He's saying I'm a terrorist.

77
00:06:28,042 --> 00:06:30,976
So, each body Poindexter drops
is just another hung on me.

78
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:34,184
Yeah. And it pisses off Fisk.
So that's like two birds, one bullet.

79
00:06:34,208 --> 00:06:36,958
Right. But he doesn't want me dead.

80
00:06:38,583 --> 00:06:40,458
I don't give a shit. He killed Foggy.

81
00:06:41,125 --> 00:06:43,851
I hope those Task Force psychos
put a bullet in his head.

82
00:06:43,875 --> 00:06:47,000
- Karen, that's not helping.
- Yeah? Well, I imagine you feel the same.

83
00:06:49,042 --> 00:06:50,208
Thank you.

84
00:06:51,375 --> 00:06:55,625
Poindexter aside, I want to take down Fisk
before there's any more collateral damage.

85
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:57,333
Okay, um...

86
00:06:57,958 --> 00:07:00,351
- We prove the Mayor was smuggling guns.
- Right.

87
00:07:00,375 --> 00:07:02,268
- Try and get the feds to file a case.
- Mmm-hmm.

88
00:07:02,292 --> 00:07:05,434
- That at least gets him out of City Hall.
- We can hope.

89
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:09,393
The Task Force shook down Cherry
once they found <i>Northern Star's</i> captain,

90
00:07:09,417 --> 00:07:11,684
which means
the First Mate's still out there.

91
00:07:11,708 --> 00:07:13,559
- We need to get to Ariana.
- Hell yeah.

92
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:15,875
So, which one of us is going to Astoria?

93
00:07:16,458 --> 00:07:17,458
How about both?

94
00:07:18,417 --> 00:07:20,083
[people chattering]

95
00:07:22,667 --> 00:07:24,792
[officer 1] Boots on the ground! Now!

96
00:07:27,625 --> 00:07:29,250
[officer 2] Suspect! Hands up!

97
00:07:35,542 --> 00:07:37,476
- [man 1] They're takin' her.
- [woman] Seriously?

98
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:39,518
[man 2] Yo, what'd she do?
Hey, what'd she do?

99
00:07:39,542 --> 00:07:41,518
- What y'all doin'?
- [officer 3] In the truck.

100
00:07:41,542 --> 00:07:43,268
- Now!
- [woman] Don't do that to her.

101
00:07:43,292 --> 00:07:44,852
- [man 3] Come on.
- [chatter continues]

102
00:07:46,042 --> 00:07:47,042
[Buck] If I may...

103
00:07:47,917 --> 00:07:49,351
[clicks tongue]

104
00:07:49,375 --> 00:07:50,458
...add a thought...

105
00:07:52,958 --> 00:07:54,125
about Daredevil.

106
00:07:55,458 --> 00:07:59,101
You know, you would have
much more influence over the situation

107
00:07:59,125 --> 00:08:01,500
if you let it be known that he

108
00:08:02,125 --> 00:08:03,458
and Matt Murdock...

109
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,333
are one and the same.

110
00:08:09,292 --> 00:08:11,542
No.

111
00:08:13,583 --> 00:08:16,333
I want to quash this idiocy, not stoke it.

112
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:20,893
Daredevil, he's an easy sell
as enemy of the people,

113
00:08:20,917 --> 00:08:22,708
but Matt Murdock? No, I--

114
00:08:23,167 --> 00:08:26,684
A blind man who saved my life?

115
00:08:26,708 --> 00:08:27,708
I don't think so.

116
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:31,208
He saved my life.

117
00:08:36,792 --> 00:08:37,893
[cameraman] Slating.

118
00:08:37,917 --> 00:08:39,875
Take... Set.

119
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:43,333
And... whenever you're ready,
Mister Mayor.

120
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:47,292
As you know, months ago,
there was an attempt on my life

121
00:08:48,042 --> 00:08:51,375
by the masked vigilante known as Bullseye.

122
00:08:52,458 --> 00:08:54,625
<i>We have reason to believe
that Matt Murdock,</i>

123
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:56,667
<i>the lawyer from Hell's Kitchen,</i>

124
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,250
<i>survived the attack on his apartment.</i>

125
00:09:00,458 --> 00:09:01,958
This is important...

126
00:09:03,417 --> 00:09:05,417
because Matt Murdock is...

127
00:09:10,458 --> 00:09:11,542
a hero.

128
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:14,351
[cell phone vibrating]

129
00:09:14,375 --> 00:09:16,792
<i>He risked his life to save mine...</i>

130
00:09:18,167 --> 00:09:20,559
only to be targeted by the same vigilantes

131
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:22,708
{\an8}that threaten our way of life.

132
00:09:23,125 --> 00:09:24,542
<i>He could be hurt.</i>

133
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:26,934
<i>He may not know who he is.</i>

134
00:09:26,958 --> 00:09:28,851
We need to get you out of here. Now.

135
00:09:28,875 --> 00:09:31,500
<i>Help find Matt Murdock, New York.</i>

136
00:09:32,125 --> 00:09:33,958
Let's bring this hero home.

137
00:09:38,833 --> 00:09:40,726
{\an8}[BB Urich] <i>What do you think
of the</i> Northern Star<i>?</i>

138
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:42,351
{\an8}[woman] <i>That boat capsized in the river?</i>

139
00:09:42,375 --> 00:09:44,059
{\an8}What a mess. How do they fix that?

140
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:46,375
{\an8}I don't know.
If you ask me, Daredevil did it.

141
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,934
{\an8}Or one of those other crazies.

142
00:09:48,958 --> 00:09:51,184
{\an8}<i>This resistance with the graffiti.</i>

143
00:09:51,208 --> 00:09:52,768
{\an8}<i>What are they resisting?</i>

144
00:09:52,792 --> 00:09:54,976
{\an8}New York's never been
this good in 30 years.

145
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,768
[♪ jaunty music playing on tablet]

146
00:09:56,792 --> 00:09:58,958
[Kingpin] <i>Uh-oh!
Looks like I spoke too soon.</i>

147
00:09:59,083 --> 00:10:00,226
<i>Someone caught me.</i>

148
00:10:00,250 --> 00:10:03,268
<i>Spoiled again by that dastardly do-gooder.</i>

149
00:10:03,292 --> 00:10:04,768
<i>I'll get him in the end.</i>

150
00:10:04,792 --> 00:10:06,851
- [Sheila] Has the Mayor seen this?
- I don't know.

151
00:10:06,875 --> 00:10:09,226
I mean, it's pretty underground, you know.

152
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:11,976
But these drops, they show up on socials,

153
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,059
then they disappear.

154
00:10:13,083 --> 00:10:14,309
It's like guerrilla shit.

155
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:15,458
Let me rephrase that.

156
00:10:15,875 --> 00:10:18,184
Are you going to show it to the Mayor?

157
00:10:18,208 --> 00:10:21,143
Yeah, I probably should,
but he's not gonna like that mask.

158
00:10:21,167 --> 00:10:22,684
No, he's not.

159
00:10:22,708 --> 00:10:25,208
These blips, they're unsubstantiated.

160
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:27,333
They're only rumor, right?

161
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:30,976
<i>The Bulletin,</i> the other majors,
they're not picking it up.

162
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,518
We shouldn't give it any oxygen.

163
00:10:32,542 --> 00:10:34,708
Who else had access to this footage?

164
00:10:35,542 --> 00:10:37,500
Buck, you, Fisk.

165
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,458
Probably Powell.

166
00:10:40,542 --> 00:10:42,934
- You?
- Yeah, me.

167
00:10:42,958 --> 00:10:44,434
Is it on your laptop?

168
00:10:44,458 --> 00:10:45,917
Hell no.

169
00:10:46,625 --> 00:10:48,125
I wouldn't do that, Sheila.

170
00:10:48,583 --> 00:10:50,292
- Come on.
- Show it to him.

171
00:10:50,917 --> 00:10:53,333
He's not a fan of surprises.

172
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:56,309
But let's be honest,
this is not just bad PR,

173
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:58,393
and it's coming from inside this building.

174
00:10:58,417 --> 00:10:59,976
Tracked the "at." Dark web.

175
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,184
It's just a leak.

176
00:11:01,208 --> 00:11:02,893
Find it, plug it, and we move on.

177
00:11:02,917 --> 00:11:04,143
It's gonna be okay.

178
00:11:04,167 --> 00:11:05,583
Thanks. Sheila?

179
00:11:06,208 --> 00:11:08,393
Look, I-- I know I can be an ass.

180
00:11:08,417 --> 00:11:10,208
I know we've had our differences, but...

181
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:14,292
- I really do respect your advice.
- I appreciate that, bubba.

182
00:11:15,042 --> 00:11:16,976
Just try and take it once in a while?

183
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,625
[indistinct chatter outside]

184
00:11:24,542 --> 00:11:25,768
[exhales heavily]

185
00:11:25,792 --> 00:11:27,208
Fuck me.

186
00:11:28,208 --> 00:11:29,488
[Matt] <i>Kind of brilliant, right?</i>

187
00:11:30,417 --> 00:11:31,542
Fisk not outing me?

188
00:11:33,083 --> 00:11:34,083
This way,

189
00:11:34,708 --> 00:11:37,851
he gets all the people
who support vigilantes

190
00:11:37,875 --> 00:11:40,268
searching for Matt Murdock
and their haters

191
00:11:40,292 --> 00:11:41,500
searching for Daredevil.

192
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:43,434
[Karen] Yeah, well... [breathing heavily]

193
00:11:43,458 --> 00:11:45,250
You're wanted by both sides now.

194
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:48,875
[chuckles softly] Huh...

195
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:52,976
[Powell] So we tripled the security
personnel here and at Gracie.

196
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:56,559
Not my call to tell you to lay low,
even with that fight next week.

197
00:11:56,583 --> 00:11:58,559
But when you or Mrs. Fisk are on the move,

198
00:11:58,583 --> 00:12:01,643
you're gonna have two full,
close protection details,

199
00:12:01,667 --> 00:12:03,917
and I'll volunteer
for one of them personally.

200
00:12:06,167 --> 00:12:09,101
I have Buck to augment my usual detail.

201
00:12:09,125 --> 00:12:10,958
Sure, no flies on Mr. Cashman.

202
00:12:11,417 --> 00:12:13,292
But, listen, Poindexter's no joke.

203
00:12:13,875 --> 00:12:15,851
He fired at you with 30 of us right there.

204
00:12:15,875 --> 00:12:18,184
You're only here
because of that prick lawyer.

205
00:12:18,208 --> 00:12:20,601
You're not much of
a politician, are you, Powell?

206
00:12:20,625 --> 00:12:21,958
I say it like I see it, sir.

207
00:12:22,583 --> 00:12:23,726
Well, here's to that.

208
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:24,792
[glasses clink]

209
00:12:25,792 --> 00:12:27,018
Murdock's an asshole.

210
00:12:27,042 --> 00:12:29,000
You want him
treated like gold, you got it.

211
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:32,268
Bullseye, if he tried once,
he'll try again.

212
00:12:32,292 --> 00:12:33,768
My guys know not to fuck around.

213
00:12:33,792 --> 00:12:35,250
They see him, they kill him.

214
00:12:35,958 --> 00:12:37,184
Same with Daredevil.

215
00:12:37,208 --> 00:12:39,042
Your dedication is impressive.

216
00:12:40,125 --> 00:12:43,208
No, I owe that red piece of shit
for what he did to my guys.

217
00:12:43,417 --> 00:12:44,768
You just want to know,

218
00:12:44,792 --> 00:12:46,309
if you go down like that,

219
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:48,542
whether someone's
gonna get payback for you.

220
00:12:50,042 --> 00:12:51,583
That's just how it works, sir.

221
00:12:52,083 --> 00:12:53,083
Yes, it is.

222
00:12:53,750 --> 00:12:56,042
Murdock's friend, the ex-cop.

223
00:12:57,083 --> 00:12:58,601
Cherry, yeah.

224
00:12:58,625 --> 00:13:00,809
Yeah. I understand he's at Metro General.

225
00:13:00,833 --> 00:13:01,917
Yeah, I'm on it.

226
00:13:02,375 --> 00:13:04,101
I got a couple other things, too.

227
00:13:04,125 --> 00:13:06,083
I'll put Matt Murdock in this office,

228
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:09,458
and I'll put Daredevil's head
on a fuckin' spike.

229
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:14,167
Either of those would be sufficient.

230
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:16,958
Well, I like to shoot the moon, sir.

231
00:13:20,083 --> 00:13:21,542
[radio beeping]

232
00:13:22,417 --> 00:13:24,542
[indistinct radio chatter]

233
00:13:26,333 --> 00:13:27,333
I just, uh...

234
00:13:32,292 --> 00:13:33,292
Cole.

235
00:13:34,208 --> 00:13:35,708
Hey, what's going on?

236
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:37,958
What are you doing here?

237
00:13:39,458 --> 00:13:40,625
I want back in, man.

238
00:13:41,250 --> 00:13:43,083
I need to be back on the Task Force.

239
00:13:43,875 --> 00:13:44,875
Yeah.

240
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:47,000
Okay. Uh...

241
00:13:47,833 --> 00:13:49,458
I mean... [chuckles softly]

242
00:13:50,542 --> 00:13:51,809
you gotta heal, man.

243
00:13:51,833 --> 00:13:54,125
This is as good as it's gonna get
for me, man.

244
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:57,059
- Look, after what they've done?
- Yeah.

245
00:13:57,083 --> 00:13:58,250
- Not just to me.
- Yeah.

246
00:13:59,292 --> 00:14:01,292
Fuck the vigilantes.

247
00:14:01,667 --> 00:14:03,375
I'm owed some get-back, brother.

248
00:14:04,083 --> 00:14:06,476
How many people died
in that asshole lawyer's place?

249
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:08,375
- Seven. Yeah, seven.
- Seven. Exactly.

250
00:14:09,583 --> 00:14:10,792
I'm fucking sure, man.

251
00:14:11,958 --> 00:14:12,958
I'm ready.

252
00:14:13,958 --> 00:14:15,101
Okay. Yeah.

253
00:14:15,125 --> 00:14:16,393
- Okay? Yeah?
- Yeah.

254
00:14:16,417 --> 00:14:17,958
Yeah, welcome back, brother.

255
00:14:18,375 --> 00:14:20,393
- Thanks. Let's get to work.
- All right.

256
00:14:20,417 --> 00:14:22,625
- [indistinct radio chatter]
- [radio beeping]

257
00:14:33,042 --> 00:14:34,768
[Bob] You guys can call it a day.

258
00:14:34,792 --> 00:14:36,143
Yeah,

259
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:38,851
- but we were told to--
- Look, I'm telling you to get lost.

260
00:14:38,875 --> 00:14:41,809
It's okay. Don't do anything
and get yourself in trouble.

261
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,976
Oh! [chuckles]

262
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,875
What the fuck is this? <i>Jurassic Park?</i>

263
00:14:46,625 --> 00:14:48,101
Just visiting an old friend.

264
00:14:48,125 --> 00:14:49,184
[McDaniel] Nice vests.

265
00:14:49,208 --> 00:14:51,708
You gonna wear
your underwear outside, too?

266
00:14:52,250 --> 00:14:53,309
Get out.

267
00:14:53,333 --> 00:14:55,726
[indistinct announcements over PA]

268
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:57,559
[monitors beeping]

269
00:14:57,583 --> 00:15:00,268
- We need backup.
- [McDaniel] Yeah, Danny said he'd stop in.

270
00:15:00,292 --> 00:15:03,101
- [Angie] Roxanne, too.
- Have her bring some Lombardi's.

271
00:15:03,125 --> 00:15:04,833
You know how bored these guys are?

272
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:08,167
You know how many more of them
are out there?

273
00:15:13,167 --> 00:15:14,958
- [Bob] We'll be back.
- We'll be here.

274
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:18,708
You bringing the pizza?
Or should we still have Roxanne do it?

275
00:15:20,208 --> 00:15:21,292
[Bob] Fuckin' hump.

276
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:26,333
Dick.

277
00:15:27,042 --> 00:15:29,393
God, I hate those little dickheads.

278
00:15:29,417 --> 00:15:30,708
[chuckles softly]

279
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:32,684
Remember McDaniel?

280
00:15:32,708 --> 00:15:34,375
Oh, yeah, I remember McDaniel.

281
00:15:35,167 --> 00:15:36,958
Word is, he was North's TO.

282
00:15:38,125 --> 00:15:39,518
- You're kidding me?
- Nope.

283
00:15:39,542 --> 00:15:41,601
- That explains a lot, man.
- Yeah?

284
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:43,101
Hey, but don't sweat it--

285
00:15:43,125 --> 00:15:44,750
[elevator bell dings]

286
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:11,333
[elevator bell dinging]

287
00:16:18,833 --> 00:16:20,917
[Powell] Fuck.
Did Cherry nose-blast the two?

288
00:16:21,458 --> 00:16:22,542
Fuck.

289
00:16:23,458 --> 00:16:25,518
You gotta be fucking-- Unbelievable.

290
00:16:25,542 --> 00:16:26,583
Stay.

291
00:16:30,917 --> 00:16:32,208
[exhales]

292
00:16:32,792 --> 00:16:34,309
[chuckling]

293
00:16:34,333 --> 00:16:35,958
[sniffles, sighs]

294
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:37,875
He's fuckin' gone.

295
00:16:39,708 --> 00:16:42,417
[Fisk] It seems this is turning into
guerrilla warfare.

296
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:43,893
[Powell] <i>So, what is this?</i>

297
00:16:43,917 --> 00:16:45,309
Is Poindexter freelancing?

298
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:47,184
Or is he in this Resistance mess?

299
00:16:47,208 --> 00:16:49,875
Without vigilantes,
there is no Resistance.

300
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:53,333
<i>Destroy one and you destroy the other.</i>

301
00:16:54,042 --> 00:16:58,643
And, Powell? Vanessa is hosting a dinner
at the mansion tonight.

302
00:16:58,667 --> 00:17:01,434
Yeah. Copy that, sir.
I already sent over four more units.

303
00:17:01,458 --> 00:17:02,917
Thank you, I appreciate that.

304
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:05,417
- Yeah.
- [cell phone beeps]

305
00:17:09,417 --> 00:17:11,018
[Fisk] You know, they say that

306
00:17:11,042 --> 00:17:13,667
driving is most dangerous after it rains.

307
00:17:16,208 --> 00:17:18,458
The collected oil, bits of rubber.

308
00:17:19,083 --> 00:17:20,792
More slippery than ice.

309
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:23,833
You're not ready for it,
and you spin out of control.

310
00:17:26,292 --> 00:17:28,625
The things that can damage us most...

311
00:17:29,792 --> 00:17:32,268
are the ones
we're least prepared for, aren't they?

312
00:17:32,292 --> 00:17:35,268
[sighs] Shit. I-- Look, I--

313
00:17:35,292 --> 00:17:37,333
I should've told you sooner. I just--

314
00:17:37,792 --> 00:17:40,143
You know, I--
I wanted to get more information

315
00:17:40,167 --> 00:17:42,583
- before coming to you because I--
- Daniel, this...

316
00:17:43,458 --> 00:17:45,625
person is mocking me.

317
00:17:46,167 --> 00:17:48,875
Yes, sir. I'm sorry, sir.

318
00:17:49,875 --> 00:17:51,143
They found this

319
00:17:51,167 --> 00:17:53,708
on Commissioner Gallo's body.

320
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:57,476
Fuckin' A.

321
00:17:57,500 --> 00:18:00,750
Do you remember
when I told you if you ever betray me...

322
00:18:02,542 --> 00:18:04,542
it'll be the last thing you ever did?

323
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:06,667
Yeah, I do.

324
00:18:07,625 --> 00:18:10,184
I wouldn't. I swear, Mayor Fisk.

325
00:18:10,208 --> 00:18:13,917
Daniel, you are
the Deputy Mayor of Communications.

326
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:17,333
- Yeah.
- Finding out how

327
00:18:17,667 --> 00:18:21,393
inside information is ending up in here

328
00:18:21,417 --> 00:18:23,351
- is your responsibility.
- Yes.

329
00:18:23,375 --> 00:18:26,018
- [loudly] Do we understand each other?
- Absolutely, sir.

330
00:18:26,042 --> 00:18:28,226
A hundred percent.
It's completely my fault--

331
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:29,958
Good. I have two questions.

332
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:32,667
Do you have any idea
where the leak came from?

333
00:18:33,458 --> 00:18:35,268
No. Honestly, sir, I don't. I--

334
00:18:35,292 --> 00:18:37,726
Is there anyone in this building
you need to protect?

335
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:38,750
Yeah.

336
00:18:39,958 --> 00:18:41,208
You.

337
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:47,583
Good answer.

338
00:18:52,458 --> 00:18:53,768
[Buck] You don't need it.

339
00:18:53,792 --> 00:18:54,851
You got me.

340
00:18:54,875 --> 00:18:59,309
And, of course, the finest security
New York taxpayers can afford.

341
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:01,208
[gun cocking]

342
00:19:03,875 --> 00:19:07,083
Have you ever been in the same room
with Benjamin Poindexter?

343
00:19:08,792 --> 00:19:09,917
Not a ballroom.

344
00:19:11,333 --> 00:19:12,750
Up close, personal?

345
00:19:13,458 --> 00:19:15,125
No, ma'am.

346
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,083
I have.

347
00:19:18,167 --> 00:19:19,934
[gun clicking]

348
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:22,000
I wouldn't call this a need,

349
00:19:22,375 --> 00:19:24,708
more like a well-thought-out...

350
00:19:25,708 --> 00:19:26,708
want.

351
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:28,250
[Buck] Hmm.

352
00:19:29,292 --> 00:19:30,625
[gun cocks]

353
00:19:35,250 --> 00:19:36,309
[gun clicks]

354
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:37,333
Good choice.

355
00:19:38,833 --> 00:19:39,833
[Vanessa] Thank you...

356
00:19:40,667 --> 00:19:41,667
Buck.

357
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:47,309
- [reporters speaking indistinctly]
- [people clamoring]

358
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:48,333
[man] Need my help?

359
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:50,417
Hey. Grab the rope.

360
00:19:52,875 --> 00:19:55,101
[indistinct chatter]

361
00:19:55,125 --> 00:19:59,226
Grab the rope, make sure to go
when they park and they dock. Come on.

362
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:00,518
[chatter continues]

363
00:20:00,542 --> 00:20:02,351
- [woman] I don't know.
- [man] Hurry up.

364
00:20:02,375 --> 00:20:04,042
Hurry up, lotta cargo here.

365
00:20:04,583 --> 00:20:06,417
Clear out the space, too.

366
00:20:06,875 --> 00:20:07,934
Come here.

367
00:20:07,958 --> 00:20:10,934
- [reporters continue indistinctly]
- [chatter continues]

368
00:20:10,958 --> 00:20:12,417
[man] Hey, Bobby.

369
00:20:14,083 --> 00:20:15,750
[sighs] It's diapers.

370
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:19,351
[chuckles] Yeah,
they weren't on the ship with me.

371
00:20:19,375 --> 00:20:21,268
- It's just a show.
- It's a good one.

372
00:20:21,292 --> 00:20:23,417
It's local salvage company. Union workers.

373
00:20:23,792 --> 00:20:26,000
It'd be a good headline. It's very, uh...

374
00:20:26,667 --> 00:20:27,875
voter-friendly.

375
00:20:30,458 --> 00:20:32,792
So, what happens
when they think no one's watching?

376
00:20:33,458 --> 00:20:35,726
[man 2] Hey, Drew, get 'em on that crane.

377
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:37,875
[chatter continues]

378
00:20:56,958 --> 00:21:00,292
I still don't understand
why would you take such a risk

379
00:21:00,958 --> 00:21:02,417
on the <i>Northern Star.</i>

380
00:21:03,083 --> 00:21:04,875
I believe that I can do...

381
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:08,750
more good than just New York.

382
00:21:09,375 --> 00:21:11,768
You have built an empire

383
00:21:11,792 --> 00:21:13,226
that will be remembered.

384
00:21:13,250 --> 00:21:15,500
Will it? New Yorkers have a short memory.

385
00:21:16,292 --> 00:21:17,292
But, yes, it...

386
00:21:18,292 --> 00:21:22,792
It's true we have built
something generational here, Vanessa.

387
00:21:23,542 --> 00:21:25,500
- But--
- Without an heir.

388
00:21:28,083 --> 00:21:30,167
We've always been enough for each other.

389
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:32,042
Yes.

390
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:34,333
Have you ever considered

391
00:21:35,250 --> 00:21:37,792
that with all that we have
and what we've done,

392
00:21:38,625 --> 00:21:42,184
that we're obligated to make
a global impact?

393
00:21:42,208 --> 00:21:43,375
[Vanessa] Hmm.

394
00:21:44,250 --> 00:21:46,042
How many more worlds

395
00:21:46,917 --> 00:21:48,333
do you need to conquer?

396
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:50,292
Hmm?

397
00:21:52,917 --> 00:21:54,125
How many are there?

398
00:21:56,667 --> 00:21:58,667
[loud chatter]

399
00:22:03,583 --> 00:22:05,625
But those are definitely not diapers.

400
00:22:07,167 --> 00:22:08,167
Shit.

401
00:22:12,708 --> 00:22:14,333
There's Task Force everywhere.

402
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:16,000
[Matt] Place is a black hole.

403
00:22:16,333 --> 00:22:19,333
If Fisk moves those guns
into Red Hook, they vanish.

404
00:22:20,583 --> 00:22:23,684
I don't think we have a choice anymore.
I gotta get into the port.

405
00:22:23,708 --> 00:22:24,708
No.

406
00:22:25,208 --> 00:22:26,583
No, Matt, it's suicide.

407
00:22:28,167 --> 00:22:29,583
It's our only shot at Fisk.

408
00:22:30,958 --> 00:22:32,268
We might not get another.

409
00:22:32,292 --> 00:22:33,292
Shit.

410
00:22:39,583 --> 00:22:40,667
I hope they find him.

411
00:22:43,250 --> 00:22:44,250
Me, too.

412
00:22:45,042 --> 00:22:46,042
He's...

413
00:22:47,292 --> 00:22:48,292
He's a good man.

414
00:22:49,958 --> 00:22:50,958
He tried.

415
00:22:57,792 --> 00:22:59,583
Sometimes I wonder if...

416
00:23:00,375 --> 00:23:04,417
If your <i>Tío</i> Hector would have never put on
that White Tiger mask,

417
00:23:05,292 --> 00:23:06,851
maybe it'd all be different.

418
00:23:06,875 --> 00:23:08,042
No, he had to.

419
00:23:08,750 --> 00:23:10,350
{\an8}- It was who he was.
- [speaking Spanish]

420
00:23:12,792 --> 00:23:14,893
[in English] If everyone was too scared
to be a hero,

421
00:23:14,917 --> 00:23:15,917
we'd have none.

422
00:23:16,417 --> 00:23:17,417
And I'd be dead.

423
00:23:24,042 --> 00:23:26,333
Hey, let's get a snack.

424
00:23:29,958 --> 00:23:31,500
[doorbell chimes]

425
00:23:34,208 --> 00:23:35,351
[indistinct chatter]

426
00:23:35,375 --> 00:23:36,375
<i>Hola,</i> Berto.

427
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:38,643
[boy] Sucks you gotta say that.

428
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:40,427
- Come on.
- [Javi] A'ight, come on. Come on.

429
00:23:48,542 --> 00:23:49,542
Angela,

430
00:23:50,042 --> 00:23:51,226
why are you so boring?

431
00:23:51,250 --> 00:23:53,268
[boys laughing]

432
00:23:53,292 --> 00:23:54,476
Look at his shoes.

433
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:57,184
Crocodile shoes.
I could hear you squeaking from outside.

434
00:23:57,208 --> 00:23:58,643
- Nah.
- I didn't even talk.

435
00:23:58,667 --> 00:24:01,268
Shut up with your
three-musketeers-from-Dollar-Tree ass.

436
00:24:01,292 --> 00:24:02,833
Hey, hey, put that back.

437
00:24:03,708 --> 00:24:05,684
{\an8}[in Spanish]

438
00:24:05,708 --> 00:24:06,708
{\an8}[chuckles]

439
00:24:08,417 --> 00:24:09,750
{\an8}[in Spanish]

440
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:20,434
- [in English] Mind your business.
- [in English] Put that back already.

441
00:24:20,458 --> 00:24:22,351
[all chattering in Spanish]

442
00:24:22,375 --> 00:24:23,792
[glass shatters]

443
00:24:25,125 --> 00:24:26,125
Berto...

444
00:24:27,375 --> 00:24:28,434
{\an8}[in Spanish]

445
00:24:28,458 --> 00:24:29,583
{\an8}[Berto in Spanish]

446
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:35,226
{\an8}[in English] Just put that down, okay?

447
00:24:35,250 --> 00:24:36,976
{\an8}[Berto in Spanish]

448
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,000
{\an8}Berto.

449
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:41,292
{\an8}[in Spanish]

450
00:24:42,792 --> 00:24:43,875
[officer grunts]

451
00:24:49,292 --> 00:24:50,292
[boy grunts]

452
00:24:52,208 --> 00:24:54,643
- [Soledad] Stop. He's a kid.
- [officer] They're thieves.

453
00:24:54,667 --> 00:24:56,518
He's taking the law into his own hands.

454
00:24:56,542 --> 00:24:59,083
- Mind your business.
- Our neighborhood is our business.

455
00:24:59,542 --> 00:25:01,393
- [officer] Hey!
- Hey! No. Don't...

456
00:25:01,417 --> 00:25:02,476
[man] Come on, man!

457
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:03,583
[officer 2] Hold him down.

458
00:25:08,417 --> 00:25:10,809
That's assaulting an officer.
You're coming with me.

459
00:25:10,833 --> 00:25:13,101
No! Get off of her! Son of a bitch!

460
00:25:13,125 --> 00:25:15,184
- Get off of her! No!
- Don't be stupid, kid.

461
00:25:15,208 --> 00:25:17,184
- [man 2] What are you doing?
- [man 3] Hey! Let her go!

462
00:25:17,208 --> 00:25:19,250
[people clamoring]

463
00:25:22,625 --> 00:25:23,750
Screw these guys!

464
00:25:24,375 --> 00:25:26,059
[man 2] Hey, what are you doing, man?

465
00:25:26,083 --> 00:25:28,583
- [clamoring intensifies]
- [glass shattering]

466
00:25:30,875 --> 00:25:32,976
[Soledad] Get home, get home,
get home, get home!

467
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:35,143
It's gonna be okay. Get home!

468
00:25:35,167 --> 00:25:36,476
Get home, okay?

469
00:25:36,500 --> 00:25:38,559
No! No!

470
00:25:38,583 --> 00:25:41,226
Get home, please! Get home safely.

471
00:25:41,250 --> 00:25:43,292
- [screaming]
- No!

472
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:45,500
No!

473
00:25:49,292 --> 00:25:51,500
[clamoring continues]

474
00:25:55,125 --> 00:25:56,542
[Javi] Get out of our neighborhood!

475
00:25:57,417 --> 00:25:59,208
Get the fuck out of our neighborhood!

476
00:26:15,917 --> 00:26:18,208
[Heather] A lot is said about
a person's mental health,

477
00:26:18,583 --> 00:26:19,708
but what about a city's?

478
00:26:20,625 --> 00:26:23,583
The randomness of a horrific crime.

479
00:26:24,833 --> 00:26:27,851
A stranger pushing another
in front of a train,

480
00:26:27,875 --> 00:26:30,750
a self-proclaimed artist

481
00:26:31,292 --> 00:26:33,250
murdering innocent people.

482
00:26:33,625 --> 00:26:36,875
How do we collectively heal
from these horrors?

483
00:26:38,250 --> 00:26:41,601
You know, you don't have to
go solo to these things.

484
00:26:41,625 --> 00:26:43,875
- [♪ soft music playing]
- [indistinct chatter]

485
00:26:45,083 --> 00:26:46,309
If I may,

486
00:26:46,333 --> 00:26:49,309
how did you and Mr. Murdock leave things?

487
00:26:49,333 --> 00:26:50,393
Not well.

488
00:26:50,417 --> 00:26:51,750
Matt was in a...

489
00:26:53,042 --> 00:26:54,042
place...

490
00:26:55,042 --> 00:26:56,167
before he got shot.

491
00:26:57,083 --> 00:27:00,542
He has very strong feelings
about your husband.

492
00:27:01,292 --> 00:27:02,833
Mr. Murdock

493
00:27:03,208 --> 00:27:07,018
always was the champion of the vigilantes.

494
00:27:07,042 --> 00:27:08,250
My husband...

495
00:27:10,750 --> 00:27:12,417
- not so much.
- [chuckles softly]

496
00:27:13,167 --> 00:27:14,167
Do you think

497
00:27:14,667 --> 00:27:16,083
Frank Castle or...

498
00:27:17,167 --> 00:27:19,101
Daredevil killed Matt?

499
00:27:19,125 --> 00:27:20,292
No, I don't.

500
00:27:23,250 --> 00:27:25,208
- Is my husband overworking you?
- No.

501
00:27:26,417 --> 00:27:27,417
Not really.

502
00:27:27,833 --> 00:27:30,333
- Vigilante trials are coming up, so...
- Hmm.

503
00:27:31,292 --> 00:27:33,875
Must be hard to get into the head of...

504
00:27:35,625 --> 00:27:36,708
those people?

505
00:27:37,417 --> 00:27:39,125
Sometimes it's a little too easy.

506
00:27:40,542 --> 00:27:41,708
That's the scary part.

507
00:27:52,042 --> 00:27:53,125
Is something wrong?

508
00:27:54,083 --> 00:27:55,143
No...

509
00:27:55,167 --> 00:27:56,208
That thing, right?

510
00:27:57,333 --> 00:28:00,351
That... sudden cold feeling.

511
00:28:00,375 --> 00:28:04,708
My gram used to say,
"That's a goose walking over your grave."

512
00:28:05,625 --> 00:28:07,625
- [laughs]
- [chuckles]

513
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:12,292
[imperceptible]

514
00:28:23,417 --> 00:28:25,018
[exhales heavily]

515
00:28:25,042 --> 00:28:26,958
[thudding on door]

516
00:28:29,750 --> 00:28:31,167
[door opens]

517
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:34,000
Hello?

518
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:54,000
Hey.

519
00:28:59,750 --> 00:29:01,708
If anybody's there, I'm not playing!

520
00:29:06,208 --> 00:29:07,208
Angela?

521
00:29:08,750 --> 00:29:10,042
How did you get in here?

522
00:29:11,125 --> 00:29:12,583
Hey, hey, what happened?

523
00:29:15,458 --> 00:29:17,083
- What happened?
- They took her.

524
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,125
They took my <i>tía.</i>

525
00:29:20,083 --> 00:29:21,750
Oh, my God. [sighs]

526
00:29:22,292 --> 00:29:23,792
Oh, come here, honey. I'm so--

527
00:29:24,792 --> 00:29:25,917
[sighs]

528
00:29:28,083 --> 00:29:31,393
- I'll start checking the jails, okay?
- No, that won't work.

529
00:29:31,417 --> 00:29:32,601
The Task Force took her,

530
00:29:32,625 --> 00:29:34,750
- and people usually disappear.
- Shit.

531
00:29:38,333 --> 00:29:39,559
- [kisses]
- [sniffles]

532
00:29:39,583 --> 00:29:40,625
[Kirsten sighs]

533
00:29:43,500 --> 00:29:44,583
That's it, isn't it?

534
00:29:46,708 --> 00:29:47,917
[Kirsten] Angela...

535
00:29:48,875 --> 00:29:50,000
Can I see it?

536
00:29:51,208 --> 00:29:52,333
[latch clicks]

537
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,684
[Kirsten] Soledad didn't want it.

538
00:30:01,708 --> 00:30:03,542
Yeah. I'm not surprised.

539
00:30:05,625 --> 00:30:07,458
Hard to be a hero these days, huh?

540
00:30:13,167 --> 00:30:15,708
[♪ mellow music playing]

541
00:30:25,667 --> 00:30:28,042
I thought we were editing <i>The BB Report.</i>

542
00:30:28,458 --> 00:30:29,833
It's a working dinner.

543
00:30:31,583 --> 00:30:35,393
Coq au vin, pommes du moutard,
and haricots vert.

544
00:30:35,417 --> 00:30:37,542
- Oh! Where from?
- Me.

545
00:30:37,958 --> 00:30:40,393
- And Julia Child.
- [scoffs]

546
00:30:40,417 --> 00:30:42,750
- Bullshit.
- Oh, truth.

547
00:30:43,208 --> 00:30:44,643
Yeah, it's a thank-you,

548
00:30:44,667 --> 00:30:47,125
you know,
for gettin' the place cleaned, and...

549
00:30:47,583 --> 00:30:48,708
a bunch of other shit.

550
00:30:49,167 --> 00:30:51,768
I mean, we both know
I wouldn't have made Deputy Mayor

551
00:30:51,792 --> 00:30:54,083
- if it wasn't for your help.
- We helped each other.

552
00:30:54,583 --> 00:30:55,583
Yeah.

553
00:30:56,667 --> 00:30:58,268
I didn't know you could cook.

554
00:30:58,292 --> 00:30:59,500
I can't.

555
00:30:59,875 --> 00:31:03,042
But I just read the directions,
did what they said.

556
00:31:03,625 --> 00:31:05,208
Hopefully, it's all right.

557
00:31:06,083 --> 00:31:08,101
I got no clue about the wine, but it was--

558
00:31:08,125 --> 00:31:10,625
It was expensive, so, hopefully it's good.

559
00:31:15,208 --> 00:31:16,268
[chuckles softly]

560
00:31:16,292 --> 00:31:17,292
Shit.

561
00:31:17,542 --> 00:31:19,833
Daniel, this is great.

562
00:31:20,333 --> 00:31:21,458
- Wow.
- Good.

563
00:31:22,208 --> 00:31:24,583
- I'm... I'm glad you like it.
- [chuckles softly]

564
00:31:25,208 --> 00:31:27,208
'Cause we got some things to figure out.

565
00:31:29,917 --> 00:31:31,958
- [knocking on door]
- Mayor Fisk?

566
00:31:48,667 --> 00:31:50,167
Were you looking for me?

567
00:31:52,250 --> 00:31:53,708
You know what that is?

568
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:56,059
Yeah.

569
00:31:56,083 --> 00:31:57,976
Some crazy shit.

570
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,250
A weird mask with Daredevil on the boat?

571
00:32:03,042 --> 00:32:05,833
That video, it came
from inside the Mayor's office.

572
00:32:06,750 --> 00:32:08,417
Maybe even off my laptop.

573
00:32:09,333 --> 00:32:10,333
Okay.

574
00:32:12,667 --> 00:32:13,875
What's your question?

575
00:32:15,708 --> 00:32:18,059
- Don't fuck with me, BB.
- [chuckles softly]

576
00:32:18,083 --> 00:32:20,309
You burned me bad
with that Mayor Garbage leak.

577
00:32:20,333 --> 00:32:22,250
Okay. That was then, and this is now.

578
00:32:22,625 --> 00:32:24,351
It's not me, seriously.

579
00:32:24,375 --> 00:32:27,143
I get it. You're a journalist,
I'm a schmuck from Staten.

580
00:32:27,167 --> 00:32:28,601
- Fuck me or whatever.
- Okay.

581
00:32:28,625 --> 00:32:31,333
But if you are leaking stuff,
anything, stop.

582
00:32:31,875 --> 00:32:32,875
It's no game.

583
00:32:33,917 --> 00:32:35,000
You could get hurt.

584
00:32:35,583 --> 00:32:36,708
We could get hurt.

585
00:32:39,958 --> 00:32:41,667
You're scared of him, aren't you?

586
00:32:43,125 --> 00:32:45,250
Politics is a brutal business, isn't it?

587
00:32:53,375 --> 00:32:54,375
Gallo...

588
00:32:55,208 --> 00:32:56,292
was a good man.

589
00:32:56,708 --> 00:32:58,875
We didn't always see eye-to-eye, but...

590
00:33:00,375 --> 00:33:01,375
I'll miss him.

591
00:33:02,042 --> 00:33:03,958
I'm just being smart.

592
00:33:06,333 --> 00:33:08,167
I wouldn't blame you if you were.

593
00:33:10,583 --> 00:33:12,018
[exhales sharply]

594
00:33:12,042 --> 00:33:14,167
I mean, you had to have asked yourself,

595
00:33:14,875 --> 00:33:16,292
what if the rumors are true?

596
00:33:17,167 --> 00:33:18,208
About Gallo?

597
00:33:18,833 --> 00:33:20,875
- About my uncle?
- [exhales deeply]

598
00:33:21,875 --> 00:33:23,917
Come on, BB. I mean, look, look at this.

599
00:33:25,125 --> 00:33:26,250
Life is good.

600
00:33:27,667 --> 00:33:28,667
I don't know, like,

601
00:33:29,292 --> 00:33:31,333
integrity can cost.

602
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:36,417
<i>Sometimes, it's better
not to know, or to ask.</i>

603
00:33:37,625 --> 00:33:39,542
You did the right thing, Miss Sheila.

604
00:33:43,583 --> 00:33:44,625
Can I walk you out?

605
00:33:45,542 --> 00:33:46,583
Yeah.

606
00:33:47,875 --> 00:33:49,643
If you are leaking stuff,

607
00:33:49,667 --> 00:33:51,268
just stop.

608
00:33:51,292 --> 00:33:52,292
Please.

609
00:33:55,875 --> 00:33:57,167
[glasses clink]

610
00:33:58,917 --> 00:34:01,018
This place was alive for a long time,

611
00:34:01,042 --> 00:34:04,750
and you three were the heart of it.

612
00:34:05,333 --> 00:34:06,583
I'm sorry.

613
00:34:07,583 --> 00:34:08,667
Shit.

614
00:34:09,500 --> 00:34:10,643
Maybe you're right.

615
00:34:10,667 --> 00:34:13,792
- [car honks in distance]
- [brakes squealing]

616
00:34:17,458 --> 00:34:18,542
[whispers] Josie...

617
00:34:22,417 --> 00:34:24,583
[car doors opening, closing]

618
00:34:27,750 --> 00:34:29,208
[knocking on door]

619
00:34:37,792 --> 00:34:39,583
- Angie?
- Josie.

620
00:34:41,417 --> 00:34:42,542
What's goin' on?

621
00:34:43,500 --> 00:34:46,476
I wanted to check up on you.
Make sure everything's all right.

622
00:34:46,500 --> 00:34:48,958
Maybe some people
are worried about Cherry.

623
00:34:49,417 --> 00:34:50,417
Don't be.

624
00:34:51,125 --> 00:34:52,208
He's safe.

625
00:34:53,167 --> 00:34:54,351
Take care.

626
00:34:54,375 --> 00:34:55,559
Lock your doors.

627
00:34:55,583 --> 00:34:56,917
Fisk is hunting.

628
00:34:57,833 --> 00:34:59,542
Resist. Rebel.

629
00:35:01,583 --> 00:35:03,583
[tape rewinding sound effect playing]

630
00:35:06,625 --> 00:35:08,976
{\an8}- [♪ fanfare plays]
- [Mayor Kingpin] It's me again,

631
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:10,309
Mayor Kingpin,

632
00:35:10,333 --> 00:35:14,226
here to give you a better,
more beautiful New York,

633
00:35:14,250 --> 00:35:17,476
<i>without all the riffraff
messin' up our city.</i>

634
00:35:17,500 --> 00:35:18,875
[people screaming]

635
00:35:19,750 --> 00:35:21,208
[man on speaker] <i>You must leave.</i>

636
00:35:22,292 --> 00:35:24,351
{\an8}[Mayor Kingpin]
I promised you a safer city,

637
00:35:24,375 --> 00:35:27,292
{\an8}and look at how safe I'm making it!

638
00:35:27,833 --> 00:35:29,625
{\an8}Rounding up all the...

639
00:35:30,792 --> 00:35:32,875
[echoing] ...vigilantes.

640
00:35:33,750 --> 00:35:35,059
[maniacal laughter]

641
00:35:35,083 --> 00:35:36,768
<i>Hiding in plain sight,</i>

642
00:35:36,792 --> 00:35:40,851
{\an8}as random people I just don't like.

643
00:35:40,875 --> 00:35:41,875
<i>Don't worry,</i>

644
00:35:42,250 --> 00:35:43,976
<i>all these people are safe</i>

645
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:46,476
with all your childhood dogs

646
00:35:46,500 --> 00:35:48,542
in a farm upstate.

647
00:35:49,250 --> 00:35:50,768
<i>And for all you rebels,</i>

648
00:35:50,792 --> 00:35:53,434
<i>the more you resist, the more you rebel,</i>

649
00:35:53,458 --> 00:35:55,750
it hurts my feelings.

650
00:35:56,500 --> 00:35:57,684
[baby crying]

651
00:35:57,708 --> 00:35:59,934
There's nothing to worry about.

652
00:35:59,958 --> 00:36:01,518
I'm keeping you safe.

653
00:36:01,542 --> 00:36:04,559
{\an8}Because, remember, I love you, New York.

654
00:36:04,583 --> 00:36:06,726
{\an8}I'm Mayor Fisk, and I approve this lie--

655
00:36:06,750 --> 00:36:08,167
{\an8}I mean, message.

656
00:36:08,583 --> 00:36:10,458
[heavy breathing]

657
00:37:31,458 --> 00:37:33,708
I know why you're hunting me.

658
00:37:39,250 --> 00:37:41,042
- [gun fires]
- [gasping]

659
00:37:45,333 --> 00:37:46,333
You okay?

660
00:37:46,875 --> 00:37:47,875
Are you okay?

661
00:37:49,708 --> 00:37:52,083
- I'm here.
- [breathing heavily]

662
00:37:53,417 --> 00:37:55,250
I can't get you into Red Hook.

663
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:58,333
You were right. It's a...

664
00:37:59,667 --> 00:38:00,833
It's a black hole.

665
00:38:03,625 --> 00:38:04,750
There has to be a way.

666
00:38:05,792 --> 00:38:06,792
Well...

667
00:38:07,333 --> 00:38:09,292
I'd prefer one where you get out alive.

668
00:38:11,417 --> 00:38:12,417
Yeah, me, too.

669
00:38:16,167 --> 00:38:17,268
[Fisk] <i>It's okay.</i>

670
00:38:17,292 --> 00:38:18,875
<i>It's going to be okay, my love.</i>

671
00:38:19,208 --> 00:38:20,292
<i>What's on your mind?</i>

672
00:38:25,417 --> 00:38:27,393
[Vanessa] I hope that one day,

673
00:38:27,417 --> 00:38:29,875
we find everything we want.

674
00:38:31,208 --> 00:38:32,792
Someplace peaceful.

675
00:38:33,542 --> 00:38:35,083
And where would that place be?

676
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:37,375
New York is our home.

677
00:38:37,792 --> 00:38:38,792
No.

678
00:38:39,958 --> 00:38:41,500
You are my home.

679
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:43,708
[Karen] You ever think we'd end up here?

680
00:38:44,250 --> 00:38:45,417
There are worse places.

681
00:38:46,792 --> 00:38:47,851
Like Brooklyn?

682
00:38:47,875 --> 00:38:50,542
[both laughing]

683
00:38:51,667 --> 00:38:52,768
That's--

684
00:38:52,792 --> 00:38:54,351
- I liked Brooklyn.
- Oh, yeah?

685
00:38:54,375 --> 00:38:55,708
My place was nice.

686
00:38:56,125 --> 00:38:57,708
[Vanessa] We still own the island.

687
00:38:58,833 --> 00:38:59,833
Yes.

688
00:39:00,125 --> 00:39:02,000
When was the last time we were there?

689
00:39:02,708 --> 00:39:05,601
I hate the feeling of sand
between my toes.

690
00:39:05,625 --> 00:39:07,250
[laughing]

691
00:39:08,625 --> 00:39:10,125
I did like it there, though.

692
00:39:11,625 --> 00:39:12,625
Anywhere with you.

693
00:39:13,667 --> 00:39:14,768
[Vanessa] Mmm.

694
00:39:14,792 --> 00:39:18,292
Do you really think that
we could live-- Thrive...

695
00:39:20,625 --> 00:39:21,958
outside of all this?

696
00:39:22,375 --> 00:39:23,375
I do.

697
00:39:25,125 --> 00:39:26,208
I have to.

698
00:39:30,042 --> 00:39:31,208
[softly] I have to.

699
00:39:33,125 --> 00:39:34,768
[Matt] <i>I do miss my records, though.</i>

700
00:39:34,792 --> 00:39:36,042
Hold that thought.

701
00:39:37,333 --> 00:39:38,809
No-- Wait. Oh!

702
00:39:38,833 --> 00:39:40,684
- [Karen] Mmm-mmm.
- [sighs]

703
00:39:40,708 --> 00:39:42,434
[♪ R&B music playing on speakers]

704
00:39:42,458 --> 00:39:43,500
What are you doing?

705
00:39:46,500 --> 00:39:47,559
Oh!

706
00:39:47,583 --> 00:39:49,792
[laughs] No way!

707
00:39:50,292 --> 00:39:52,018
<i>Vive le resistance.</i>

708
00:39:52,042 --> 00:39:53,083
[laughs]

709
00:39:57,625 --> 00:39:59,708
<i>♪ In the fire ♪</i>

710
00:40:01,125 --> 00:40:03,792
<i>♪ It was burning ♪</i>

711
00:40:04,708 --> 00:40:07,542
<i>♪ Sweetheart, I know... ♪</i>

712
00:40:08,625 --> 00:40:11,917
- [vehicles approaching]
- [distant thudding]

713
00:40:12,875 --> 00:40:13,875
Hold on.

714
00:40:15,875 --> 00:40:17,309
[officer on speakers] <i>On my mark.</i>

715
00:40:17,333 --> 00:40:18,976
- [high-pitched ringing]
- [Matt groaning]

716
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:21,684
<i>- This is the Anti-Vigilante Task Force.</i>
- Hey.

717
00:40:21,708 --> 00:40:24,768
<i>We have you surrounded.
Come out or we'll be forced to remove you.</i>

718
00:40:24,792 --> 00:40:26,226
- [officer 2] Go!
- [officer 3] Hands up!

719
00:40:26,250 --> 00:40:27,851
[Josie] Get off of me!

720
00:40:27,875 --> 00:40:29,226
[Matt] They have Josie. Stay here.

721
00:40:29,250 --> 00:40:30,450
- Stay low!
- [Karen] Yeah, go.

722
00:40:31,125 --> 00:40:32,726
[sirens wailing]

723
00:40:32,750 --> 00:40:35,958
[officer 1] <i>Vigilantism will not
be tolerated in this city.</i>

724
00:40:36,917 --> 00:40:39,643
<i>- This is the Anti-Vigilante Task Force.</i>
- [Josie] All right.

725
00:40:39,667 --> 00:40:42,976
<i>We have you surrounded.
Come out or we'll be forced to remove you.</i>

726
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:44,268
[Daredevil grunting]

727
00:40:44,292 --> 00:40:46,917
<i>- Any and all resistance will be--</i>
- [high-pitched ringing]

728
00:40:48,125 --> 00:40:49,417
Go somewhere safe.

729
00:40:52,042 --> 00:40:53,500
[officer 4] Clear every floor!

730
00:40:56,375 --> 00:40:57,434
- [Karen] Hey.
- Hey, hey, hey.

731
00:40:57,458 --> 00:40:59,083
[grunting]

732
00:41:00,792 --> 00:41:02,833
[all grunting]

733
00:41:10,750 --> 00:41:12,833
[♪ music continues playing]

734
00:41:19,542 --> 00:41:21,875
- [Daredevil yelling]
- [all grunting]

735
00:41:56,583 --> 00:41:58,393
[panting]

736
00:41:58,417 --> 00:41:59,875
[sirens wailing]

737
00:42:01,792 --> 00:42:02,792
Karen!

738
00:42:04,125 --> 00:42:05,309
Karen!

739
00:42:05,333 --> 00:42:07,375
[continues panting]

740
00:42:10,042 --> 00:42:11,750
<i>Karen!</i>

741
00:42:44,875 --> 00:42:46,768
[Karen sighs]

742
00:42:46,792 --> 00:42:49,167
- [Daredevil] Where were you?
- I know. I know. Just...

743
00:42:49,708 --> 00:42:50,917
- Come on.
- What happened?

744
00:42:51,958 --> 00:42:53,417
I have something to show you.

745
00:43:15,125 --> 00:43:16,125
What did you do?

746
00:43:17,208 --> 00:43:18,375
They're hunting us.

747
00:43:19,417 --> 00:43:21,292
Maybe it's time we started hunting them.

748
00:43:22,292 --> 00:43:23,833
[Daredevil breathing heavily]

